Class AsynchMessageRoute

    @CamelConfiguration(value="msgRouteBean")
public class AsynchMessageRoute
extends AbstractBasicRoute
    Route definition that processes asynchronous message taken from message queue.

    Some "well-known" URIs:

    • AsynchConstants.URI_ERROR_FATAL
    • AsynchConstants.URI_ASYNC_MSG

      • isMessageObsolete

        @Handler
public boolean isMessageObsolete(@Body
                                          Message msg)
        Checks if current message wasn't converted to other state. It can happen when message is long time in queue that repairing process converts message back to PARTLY_FAILED state and evenly message can start with duplicate processing.
        Parameters:
        msg - the message
        Returns:
        true when message is in wrong state false otherwise
